    "location": "Victoria Park, Causeway Bay",
    "context": "Mid-Autumn Festival (中秋節) falls on the 15th day of the eighth lunar month. Hong Kong families gather in parks with lanterns, mooncakes, and candles. Victoria Park in Causeway Bay hosts the biggest public celebration. The atmosphere is festive and relaxed. You've bumped into your neighbour's family at the park gathering.",
    "cultural_note": "Almost every year since 1880, the Tai Hang neighbourhood (大坑) has performed the Fire Dragon Dance for three nights of the Mid-Autumn Festival, a 67-metre dragon skeleton packed with some 72,000 lit incense sticks, carried by hundreds of volunteers through narrow streets. The ritual began to ward off plague. It has paused only rarely, most recently for the pandemic, and was inscribed on China's national intangible cultural heritage list in 2011.",
